text: Nuno Gomes Nabiam (born 17 November 1966) is a Bissau-Guinean politician. He was the Prime Minister of Guinea-Bissau from 28 February 2020 to 8 August 2023. On 29 April 2020, he and three ministers tested positive for COVID-19. ==References== Category:1966 births Category:Living people Category:Prime Ministers of Guinea-Bissau Category:Current national leaders
